INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4300','letter','1786-01-04','Richmond','VA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','Although I was compelled, by duty, to lay before the Council your answer to my notification of your appointment to Philadelphia, I was happy to find them concurring with me in the propriety of entreating you not to decide on a refusal immediately.','ltr_edr4300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4301','letter','1786-03-02','Richmond','VA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','You may possibly be surprised, that a work, which has already expended a considerable sum of money, should be delineated in so few words as the copies now sent contain.','ltr_edr4301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4302','letter','1786-12-06','Richmond','VA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','What our enemies have foretold, seems to be hastening to its accomplishment ; and cannot be frustrated but by an instantaneous, zealous, and steady union among the friends of the Federal Government.','ltr_edr4302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4303','letter','1789-12-06','Richmond','VA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','When I had the honor of writing to you last, the amendments had, I believe, been under consideration in a Committee of the Whole, and ten were adopted, and the two last rejected.','ltr_edr4303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4304','letter','1792-01-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','By the papers, which I have now the honor of returning to you, a wish seems to be expressed that the President should recommend to Congress a digest of federal law, the appointment of one person only to such a service, and the selection of the author of those papers for that work.','ltr_edr4304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4305','letter','1793-02-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','Convulsed as we are, I cannot but believe that there is scarcely a man in the Government, whom party will not, sooner or later, destine for an attack.','ltr_edr4305.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4306','letter','1793-02-22','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','I do myself the honor of presenting to you some of those views, which the very delicate affair of the removal affords, and the result of a provisional inquiry which I set on foot.','ltr_edr4306.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4307','letter','1794-01-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','I do myself the honor of inclosing to you a certificate from Judge Wilson, of my having qualified as Secretary of State.','ltr_edr4307.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4308','letter','1794-01-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have examined all Mr. Morris\'s ministerial correspondence ; and, after the impression which I had received from others, whom I supposed to be conversant with it, I am really astonished to find so little of what is exceptionable','ltr_edr4308.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4309','letter','1794-04-06','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','I conclude, from what you observed yesterday, that, in the nomination of an Envoy Extraordinary to London, you prefer some statement more special than is customary in nominations.','ltr_edr4309.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_edr4310','letter','1794-10-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Edmund','Randolph','','George','Washington','','individual','','There is nothing so little talked of as the yellow fever. I believe that I am almost the only inquirer after it','ltr_edr4310.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
